This paper deals with the problem of estimating facial reflectance and geometry from images, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of 3D models and optimization techniques, which are commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in generating photorealistic facial images, which could be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and robotics (cs.RO).
